    "This step is crucial for developing robust initial representations for each modality, ensuring that the model can effectively handle the variety and complexity of multimodal inputs.",
    "2) Implementation of Modified Loss Function: The training utilizes a modified loss function designed to emphasize cross-modal coherence.",
    "This adaptation ensures that the model does not disproportionately favor one modality over others and maintains a balanced learning trajectory across all types of input.",
    "The loss function integrates terms that penalize disparities in learning rates and accuracies across different modalities.",
    "3) Distributed Training Techniques: To address the increased computational demand inherent in processing multimodal data, distributed training techniques are applied."
